title: The Book of World-Famous music (classical, popular and folk).pdf
description:
Crown Publishers | 1966 | Pdf | Eng | 564 pages | 119 MB

Acknowledged the most comprehensive reference work of the world's best-known music ever assembled, The Book of World-Famous Music is a fascinatmg compendium of 500 years of musical scholarship, anecdote, and history. Now greatly enlarged and  thoroughly revised, the book traces almost 1,000 of the world's most famous melodies back to their original printed sources
